Technology Brief -- Western Digital Corp.:
   Loss in Fiscal 2nd Quarter
   Narrowed to $20.4 Million
The maker of computer disk drive products said revenue
fell 5.9% to $216.3 million from $230 million.
   Roger W. Johnson, chairman, president and chief executive
officer, said, "There's no way our continuing losses can be
called acceptable." But he said that the latest results
"reflect some very positive operational trends," including
substantial improvements in its disk drive business.
   In New York Stock Exchange trading yesterday, Western
Digital shares were up 12.5 cents to $4.125.